# Risuai — Cursor Context

# Full project reference: AGENTS.md

## Stack
- Svelte 5 (Runes: $state, $derived, $effect, $props) + TypeScript 5.9
- Vite 7 + Tailwind CSS 4 + Tauri 2.9 (Rust)
- pnpm, Vitest + fast-check, strict: false

## Path Alias
- `src` → `/src` (use `import { x } from 'src/ts/...'`)

## Key Files
- `src/ts/stores.svelte.ts` — Reactive state (DBState, selectedCharID)
- `src/ts/storage/database.svelte.ts` — Data model (Database, character, Chat, Message)
- `src/ts/process/index.svelte.ts` — Chat pipeline (sendChat)
- `src/ts/process/request/` — API requests (OpenAI, Anthropic, Google)
- `src/ts/plugins/plugins.svelte.ts` — Plugin system
- `src/ts/globalApi.svelte.ts` — Utility functions
- `src/ts/alert.ts` — Error system (alertError)
- `src/App.svelte` — Root (conditional rendering, no router)
- `src/lang/index.ts` — i18n (import { language })

## Directory Layout
- `src/ts/` — Business logic
- `src/lib/` — Svelte UI components
- `src/lang/` — i18n
- `src-tauri/` — Rust desktop
- `server/` — Self-hosting (Node.js, Hono)
- `plugins/` — Plugin files

## File Extensions
- `.svelte` — UI components (PascalCase)
- `.svelte.ts` — Reactive TS with runes (camelCase)
- `.ts` — Pure TypeScript (camelCase)

## Rules
- Read files before editing
- Match existing code style
- Use `src/` alias for imports
- Use alertError() for errors, never silent catch
- Use language.xxx for user-facing strings
- New code: Svelte 5 Runes ($props, $state, $derived, $effect)
- Run `pnpm check` after changes
- Colocate tests as *.test.ts
- No console.log in production
- Prefer immutability (new objects, not mutation)

## Commands
- `pnpm dev` — Dev server (5174)
- `pnpm check` — Type check
- `pnpm test` — Tests
- `pnpm build` — Production build
- `pnpm tauri dev` — Desktop dev
